observations.recommendation:
a. The Property Officer and the Municipal Accountant maintain property cards and property ledger cards, respectively and update them periodically to aid the conduct of physical count of PPE;
b. The Inventory Committee conduct a complete physical count of all PPE excluding CIP annually and prepare the required reports thereof;
c. The Inventory Committee see to it that only tangible items with costs of with costs of ₱50,000.00 and above are included as PPE in compliance with COA Circular No. 2024-006;
d. Thereafter, the Property Officer and the Municipal Accountant reconcile the physical count reports with the balances of PPE accounts per books to establish the correct balances that should be presented in the financial statements; and
e. Management avail of the opportunity provided by the COA for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances by following the procedures and guidelines set in COA Circular 2020-006.

We reiterated our recommendation that:

The Management create an Inventory Committee;

The Inventory Committee conduct the physical count of the LGU’s PPE;




The Inventory Committee prepare the RPCPPE and furnish a copy to the Office of the Auditor;



The Property Officer reconcile property cards maintained with the RPCPPE and discrepancies be verified and adjusted; and



The Municipal Accountant likewise reconcile PPE ledger cards and other accounting records with the property cards and the RPCPPE.

